{{#> base/base selected="about"}}
<div class="caseLayout">
    <div class="caseLeft">
        <h1 class="caseTitleLeft">About</h1>
        <hr class="caseRule">
        <img src="img/sophie_durand.jpg" alt="Sophie Durand" class="aboutPhoto">
        <div class="caseMeta">
            <div class="caseMetaItem caseMetaFull">
                <span class="caseMetaLabel">Location</span>
                <span class="caseMetaValue">Stockholm, Sweden</span>
            </div>
            <div class="caseMetaItem caseMetaFull">
                <span class="caseMetaLabel">Currently</span>
                <span class="caseMetaValue">Lead Product Designer @Acast</span>
            </div>
            <div class="caseMetaItem caseMetaFull">
                <span class="caseMetaLabel">Education</span>
                <div class="caseMetaValue">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Software Engineering — Telecom SudParis</li>
                        <li>HCI — Blekinge Tekniska Högskola</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="caseMetaItem caseMetaFull">
                <span class="caseMetaLabel">Experience</span>
                <span class="caseMetaValue">13 years</span>
            </div>
            <div class="caseMetaItem caseMetaFull">
                <span class="caseMetaLabel">Previously worked with</span>
                <div class="caseMetaValue">
                    <ul>
                        <li>H&M</li>
                        <li>Thomas Cook</li>
                        <li>BBC</li>
                        <li>Sainsbury's</li>
                        <li>Japan Airlines</li>
                        <li>Amadeus IT Group</li>
                        <li>and more</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="caseRight">
        <div class="caseParagraphe">
            <div class="caseParagrapheContent">
                <p>Hiya! I'm Sophie, a Product Designer based in <strong>Stockholm</strong>. I'm originally from the north-east of <strong>France</strong>, and I lived in the <strong>UK</strong> for a while before settling in Sweden.</p>
                <p>I love <strong>figuring out how people work and think</strong>, and turning that into products that are intuitive, and genuinely useful. Whether I'm designing an experience or collaborating with teams, I'm obsessed with <strong>simplicity and efficiency</strong>.</p>
                <p>When I'm not working, I'm usually with my husband and our two sons (7 and 4), playing a strategy <strong>board game</strong> or <strong>reading</strong> way too much (I'm in two book clubs, where "gentle" discussions get surprisingly heated). And of course, I love listening to <strong>podcasts</strong>!</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        {{#> case/paragraphe title="Background"}}
            <p>I'm currently a Lead Product Designer at <a href="https://www.acast.com/en-us">Acast</a>, building products for content creators and sellers, and driving cross-team initiatives to improve the experience across our product offering.</p>
            <p>I've worked at <a href="https://www2.hm.com/en_gb/index.html">H&M</a>, travel company <a href="https://www.thomascook.com/">Thomas Cook</a>, UX consultancy <a href="https://www.system-concepts.com/">System Concepts</a>, and technology provider <a href="https://amadeus.com/en">Amadeus</a>.</p>
            <p>I studied <strong>Software Engineering</strong> at <a href="https://www.telecom-sudparis.eu/">Telecom SudParis</a> and <strong>Human-Computer Interaction</strong> at <a href="https://www.bth.se/eng/">Blekinge Tekniska Högskola</a>.</p>
        {{/case/paragraphe}}

        {{#> case/paragraphe title="What my colleagues say"}}
            <blockquote class="aboutQuote">
                <p>"Sophie is very <strong>thoughtful</strong> with everything she does, this is so useful for the teams that have a tendency to dive in and want to build the next cool thing. The <strong>'push back' never feels like a correction</strong>, the whole team is taken along on the decision."</p>
                <cite>Engineering Manager</cite>
            </blockquote>
            <blockquote class="aboutQuote">
                <p>"Sophie is <strong>driving design quality</strong> in her teams, and <strong>structured conversations across teams</strong>. She makes explorations, different directions, and reasoning visible in Miro boards, looms, or documents. It's really useful to have reasoning documented, to be able to build on it and have actual artifacts to discuss. She <strong>articulates her points well</strong>, and is thoughtful about how she presents arguments."</p>
                <cite>Product Designer</cite>
            </blockquote>
            <blockquote class="aboutQuote">
                <p>"Sophie is a very skilled designer and she obviously knows her craft very well. When we're thrown a technical or business curveball which means we need to re-think scope, Sophie is so <strong>pragmatic</strong> about what we can cut to make sure we can stay on track and hit our goals. She's a <strong>strong champion of the user</strong>, and makes sure our planning and prioritisation sessions have a clear user focus."</p>
                <cite>Product Manager</cite>
            </blockquote>
        {{/case/paragraphe}}
    </div>
</div>
{{/base/base}}
